`127.0.0.1:18332`.\n5.  **Verify Python script:** Ensure `RPC_HOST`, `RPC_PORT`, `RPC_USER`, and `RPC_PASSWORD` are set exactly as they are configured in `bitcoin.conf` (with `RPC_PORT` being 18332). Save the script.\n6.  **Run the Python script again.**\n\nThe `WinError 10061` strongly suggests the issue lies with Bitcoin Core\u0027s RPC listener not being available or correctly configured for `127.0.0.1:18332` when the Python script tries to connect. Check the `debug.log` first after restarting Bitcoin Core; it\u0027s often the most helpful diagnostic step.",
